	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52758><span id= >Hjorthen</span></a><br><span id=notbold>29 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.16]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>First of all, DEX does not control disrupts and fizzles. <br><br>Secondly, disrupts and fizzles are two completely different things (although the result in-game is very much the same =).<br><br>Your fizzle rate depends ONLY on your skill level in the school of the spell which you try to cast. So casting root with a skill level of 5 in alteration will leave you with a very high fizzle rate.<br><br>Disrupts depends ONLY on your channelling skill level. The higher your channelling skill, the higher the chance of regaining your concentrating and continue casting.<br><br>Not flaming, just trying to clear out a common misunderstanding. =)</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
